Wrong. Alot of people misread this, but its not true. Its SUPPOSED to do at least <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 4x the weapons base damage</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. From the EQ-Manual in the EQ-Directory:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> INNERFLAME (Level 56): When using this discipline, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> all hits landed by the monk will be for at least four times the base weapons/hand damage. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And it does that, and even more, because it basically makes your Min Hit= (4x weapon base damage ) +  Weapon Damage Bonus, instead of the normal ( Base Weapon Damage / 10 ) + Weapon Damage Bonus.<br>
<br>
